							<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I play a dirge on Najena.  It's really hard to answer any of your specific questions with any accuracy - I think dirges and troubs are more or less equally rare on my server.  As for group/raid utility, in general they were pretty even in groups with troubs having something of an edge on raids.  I think that's evened out a bit since the combat changes.  Dirge debuffs were kind of unleashed by the concentration issues and that certainly helps them catch up to the utility edge troubs had with stacking buffs.  I think the edge dirges had in soloing has also been evened out quite a bit since the patch, but I have to admit I've never played a troub.  But the real big guns dirges had are not quite as dominant and they beefed up troub damage enough that I think both solo pretty comfortably now.  There are no sub-class specific quests I know of and in fact, I really don't even know of bard-specific quests.
<br />

<br />
So all in all, I really don't think there is any categorical reason to prefer one over the other at this time.  Look over the spell lists and get a feel for what they do.  The big differences are:
<br />

<br />
Dirges - stronger debuffs of enemies, noxious resists and damage, lifetaps.
<br />
Troubs - stronger buffs of allies, elemental resists and damage, power taps.
<br />

<br />
At this time, I think the differences are more about style than actual playability or utility.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.mausturm.com/EQ2/images/dingsig1.jpg"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
