							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Our guild has a level 50 + trouby now. I have grouped with her in melee heavy group and it rocks....we can do a bit of Crowd Control...her cc with mez is better than my fear, but with fear, you pretty much know which one I'm fearing. At any rate, we can lock down 2, which is good enough for most fights (since cc is kinda rare in EQII anyway)...in addition, we don't die like chanters if we get a few resists and draw aggro.
<br />

<br />
I have grouped with her and an enchanter (coercer) in the group. We still have full concentration buffs up for both of us. We can help the chanter if hes getting resisits.
<br />

<br />
The amazing thing, doing the same content, it still seems to go just as quickly with 2 bards and a chanter in the group as it does with a more standard group makeup. Group DPS and Functionality just didn't suffer.
<br />

<br />
Anyone who has read my post knows I'm disinclined to cut SOE a lot of slack, however.....
<br />

<br />
If balance is what you are after, it exists in EQII...that group in EQI, in most cases, would not have functioned well.<br />_________________<br />Krescendo, 60 Kerran Dirge--Faydark
